<text>Self-running demo: How to build a 2D molecule

Back to: &lt; Building Radial Bonds | Building Angular Bonds &gt;

Click the left button below the window to start a self-running demo of how to build a 2D molecule. When it is completed, just press the button again to replay. Do not disturb the demo while it is running --- each step pauses for one or two seconds. Wait until it finishes. You can press the right button to clear everything and try to use the buttons on the tool bar to create molecules of your own, after you have watched how molecules are made.

Hit the &quot;Show me how...&quot; button below this container, and
WAIT and WATCH the demo until it completes.

 
  

This is a self-running demo played by MW scripts. Here is the source, which can be a helpful reference if you are interested in learning how to use scripts to create powerful models and elegant user interfaces.

To save the source script, just open it and then save it. Do not change the file extension (.mws).

Want to see more self-running demos?

Back to: &lt; Building Radial Bonds | Building Angular Bonds &gt;</text>
